explanation: This solution uses dynamic programming to calculate the number of distinct sequences Bob can use to beat Alice. It iterates over the string s and for each character, it updates the dp array to store the number of distinct sequences that can be used to beat Alice up to that point. Finally, it calculates the total number of distinct sequences Bob can use to beat Alice by summing up the differences between the dp array and the dp array shifted by the index of the current character.

